[The best protection is to vaccinate your horse, use sprays for flies and mosquitoes that are approved for horses, and clean up any standing water where mosquitoes can breed. But first and foremost is to vaccinate your horse.

We don't hear of too many deer with EEE. I wonder why they tested it for that particular disease? - Mod.TG

The state of Massachusetts can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2881156,42000. Worcester and Bristol counties can be seen on the map at http://geology.com/county-map/massachusetts-county-map.gif. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
